        <td width="46%" valign="top" bgcolor="#FF9999"><h3>Expected Behavior 
            </h3></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="20%" valign="top"><p>Text or Links with Focus</td>
        <td width="34%" valign="top"><p>The previous implementation of one pixel 
            doted out line was difficult to see but was not easily confused 
            with selection.<br> <br> The contrasting color ensures visibility 
            when the back ground is not white.</td>
        <td width="46%" valign="top"><ul type="disc">
                <li>Text: Double pixel dotted line. Text color should remain 
                in the unvisited links color until the link has been activated. 
                The color of the dots in the outline by default should be in 
                a contrasting color from the back ground. <font color="maroon">The 
                color and pattern are skinable and in this manner comply with 
                the W3C Accessibility guidelines.</font> <br> &nbsp; 
                <li>The text bellow shows how text with focus would look.&nbsp; 
                
            </ul>
            <p><img src="text.gif" align="bottom" width="198" height="57" border="0"> 
