            <blockquote><p><img src="Slide1.GIF" align="left" width="218" height="214"
                 border="0"></blockquote></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="20%" valign="top"><p>Image Maps and Images</td>
        <td width="34%" valign="top"><p>The consistent look of the image, map 
            and text focus indicator is also consistent with the behavior.<br> 
            <br> Image dot pattern was increased to 3 pixels as it is more visible 
            and distinct for pictures.&nbsp;</td>
        <td width="46%" valign="top"><p>Image Maps and Images: Select perimeter 
            of image map region with 3 pixel dotted line. The color of the dots 
            in the outline by default should be in a contrasting color from 
            the back ground. <font color="maroon">The color and pattern are 
            skinable and in this manner comply with the W3C Accessibility guidelines.</font> 
            </p>
            <blockquote><p><img src="Slide2.GIF" align="bottom" width="216" height="219"
                 border="0"> </blockquote></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="20%" valign="top"><p>Image Maps and Images with non black 
            and white background</td>
        <td width="34%" valign="top"><p>The contrasting color ensures visibility 
            when the back ground is not white.<br> <br> This shows how a contrasting 
            color would look.&nbsp;</td>
        <td align="left" valign="top" style="margin-left:0;"><blockquote><p align="left">Image 
                Maps and Images: Select outside perimeter of image map region 
                with 3 pixel dotted line.The<font color="maroon"> color and 
                pattern are skinable and in this manner comply with the W3C 
                Accessibility guidelines.</font></p>
                <p align="left">The color of the dots in the outline should 
                be in a contrasting color from the back ground.<img src="piggy.gif"
