    <tr>
        <td width="20%" valign="top"><p>Label and Control relationship</td>
        <td width="34%" valign="top"><p>Thought the behavior is not consistent 
            with previous behavior of showing focus it does disambiguate the 
            relationship between label and control. The user is less likely 
            to misunderstand what the control is used for. Or to select a control 
            by mistake. (See the section on <a href="#Select">Selecting a Control 
            with Focus</a>, <a href="#Drop%20Box">Selecting in a Drop Box</a> 
            and <a href="#Radio%20Buttons">Selecting a Radio Button</a> for 
            behavior.)</p>
            <p><span style="background-color:rgb(0,204,255);">Origionally we 
            wanted to show the relationship between the radio buttons in a group 
            by showing focus around the group. But due to technological limitations 
            and current convention each radio button will show focus individually.</span></td>
        <td width="46%" valign="top"><p>Visual indication for check boxes, drop 
            boxes, text fields and will be indicated by the same two pixel dotted 
