<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>My Sidebar Navigation</h2>
<p><a name="My%20Sidebar%20navigation">My Sidebar Navigation includes: how to 
open, navigate to, navigate within, and activate panels and content.</a></p>
<p>The My Sidebar content behaves similarly to web pages.</p>
<p>The Panels behave similarly to drop boxes.</p>
<p>The Space bar when the panels have focus collapses and expands the the panels. 
If the panel with focus is open it collapses the panels. If the panel with focus 
is closed it will open the panel.</p>
<p>Navigation runs like this: to get to the Sidebar tab through every thing 
or use Ctrl+(specified key), use the up and down arrow keys to direct focus 
to previous or next panel. use Space bar to select/open a panel that is closed, 
tab into the content, use web page navigation techniques here. To get to another 
panel, Shift+Tab to beginning of panel content and up to panel header to give 
panel header focus or use Ctrl+(specified key) to get to do the same thing and 
use arrows to go through the panel header. 
